WARWICK, R.I. (WLNE) — Two separate crashes startled a Warwick neighborhood on Wednesday morning. A car crashed into a house on Elmwood Avenue shortly after 6 a.m. An ABC 6 News crew saw a heavily damaged white car behind yellow police tape. Debris from the crash scattered the sidewalk. Debris from a crash into a house on Elmwood Avenue in Warwick spills into the street, Wednesday, Nov. 29, 2023. (WLNE) The homeowners told ABC 6 on scene that a van crashed into the house and the parked white car. They said the van was swerving onto the main road when it entered their yard and hit their car, which was parked near the house. Police did not immediately confirm, but ABC 6 saw a van with heavy front-end damage on scene. A heavily damaged van is towed away from the scene of a crash into a house in Warwick, Wednesday, Nov. 29, 2023. (WLNE) As police were investigating that crash, a car collided with a pole on the same street. Police said the two crashes were unrelated. It was unknown if there were any injuries. No further information was immediately available.
